            "answer_text": "Let [math]\\Delta_1=a_{11}, \\Delta_2=\\begin{vmatrix} a_{11} & a_{12} \\\\ a_{21} & a_{22}\\end{vmatrix},\\dots,\\Delta_n=\\begin{vmatrix} a_{11} & \\cdots & a_{1n} \\\\ \\vdots & \\ddots & \\vdots \\\\ a_{n1} & \\cdots & a_{nn}\\end{vmatrix}[/math] - so called leading principal minors of the matrix. The LU decompositions exists iff [math]\\Delta_i \\neq 0, i\\in\\{1,\\dots,n\\}[/math] UPD.: Nemo Y , it is usually assumed that the matrix is non-degenerate for the LU decomposition. ",
